      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Drinking extra water alone will not fix these symptoms and, in fact, can lead to dangerous lithium toxicity if your kidneys can't process the excess fluid. You need to see your doctor immediately to adjust your dosage, as unmonitored lithium levels can cause permanent organ damage or life-threatening seizures. Please call your healthcare provider right away, even if you feel like you can manage it on your own.",
